From Figma to Claude Code and back
Brought to you by Optimizely [ https://substack.com/redirect/ec8b033d-d1ba-=
483f-aa9f-3bb1a5b35e60?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMWp1ZGpwIn0.5o04gUnkd-Msu0Ib_nbCOLc-sw15=
-DjXlvGx8bWpSeo ]=E2=80=94Your AI agent orchestration platform for marketin=
g and digital teams
Gui Seiz [ https://substack.com/redirect/eba98897-2c72-4773-b7a4-5245d61ec3=
76?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMWp1ZGpwIn0.5o04gUnkd-Msu0Ib_nbCOLc-sw15-DjXlvGx8bWpSeo ] (d=
esigner) and Alex Kern [ https://substack.com/redirect/61e49f0b-8d88-4823-8=
18a-0d71067d5356?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMWp1ZGpwIn0.5o04gUnkd-Msu0Ib_nbCOLc-sw15-DjXlv=
Gx8bWpSeo ] (engineer) from Figma show how to pull a live interface from pr=
oduction, staging, or localhost into Figma, turn it into editable design fr=
ames, explore variations collaboratively, and push changes back into code u=
sing Claude Code and MCPs=E2=80=94creating a continuous design =E2=86=94 co=
de loop.
Listen now on YouTube [ https://substack.com/redirect/94345c6c-1fde-42eb-90=
6e-de9f4eda8766?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMWp1ZGpwIn0.5o04gUnkd-Msu0Ib_nbCOLc-sw15-DjXlvG=
